        <abstract>
            <p>Encloses letter concerning Edward Blyth’s application for a position with the China expedition.</p> 
<p>Mentions reviews of the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>. Guesses that Huxley wrote the <hi rend="italic">Times</hi> review.</p>  
<p>Alludes to discussion of relations between fossil and modern types [in <hi rend="italic">Principles of geology</hi> 3: 144].</p> 
            <p>Discusses destruction of tropical forms in the glacial period.</p>
            <p>Mentions letter from Dana concerning Dana’s illness.</p>
        </abstract>
